Company Overview of Entegrion, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Entegrion, Inc. designs, develops, and delivers healthcare products for military healthcare, and commercial applications. The company provides Stasix, a pharmaceutical agent that is derived from human platelets, which offers cellular hemostatic function; Resusix that inactivates harmful viruses, such as hepatitis A, B, and HIV; Portable Coagulation Monitor, a handheld point-of-care device for the assessment of clotting disorders, empirical evidence of trauma-induced coagulopathy, and response to therapy; and Multi-Functional Resuscitation Fluid that addresses critical blood replacement needs. The company was formerly known as Hemocellular Therapeutics, Inc. and changed its name to Entegrion,...
Entegrion, Inc. designs, develops, and delivers healthcare products for military healthcare, and commercial applications. The company provides Stasix, a pharmaceutical agent that is derived from human platelets, which offers cellular hemostatic function; Resusix that inactivates harmful viruses, such as hepatitis A, B, and HIV; Portable Coagulation Monitor, a handheld point-of-care device for the assessment of clotting disorders, empirical evidence of trauma-induced coagulopathy, and response to therapy; and Multi-Functional Resuscitation Fluid that addresses critical blood replacement needs. The company was formerly known as Hemocellular Therapeutics, Inc. and changed its name to Entegrion, Inc. in 2004. Entegrion, Inc. was founded in 2002 and is based in Research Triangle Park, North Carolina.
